were, while we are falcons that are not drawn to this amazing bait, but look down to the earth for \softline
our temptations.  Compare that other disobedient falcon, the monster Geryon, at }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Inferno}{\plain \fs24 \f1  \softline
XVII.127-132.  The language of this passage is Boethian.  See }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 De consolatione philosophiae}{\plain \fs24 \f1  \softline
